us.ihmc.euclid.referenceFrame.interfaces

Interface FrameVector4DBasics

  • All Superinterfaces:
    us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Clearable, FixedFrameTuple4DBasics, FixedFrameVector4DBasics, FrameChangeable, FrameTuple4DBasics, FrameTuple4DReadOnly, FrameVector4DReadOnly, ReferenceFrameHolder, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Transformable, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple4D.interfaces.Tuple4DBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple4D.interfaces.Tuple4DReadOnly, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple4D.interfaces.Vector4DBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple4D.interfaces.Vector4DReadOnly
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FrameVector4D

    public interface FrameVector4DBasics
extends FixedFrameVector4DBasics, FrameTuple4DBasics, FrameChangeable
    Write and read interface for a 4D vector expressed in a changeable reference frame, i.e. the reference frame in which this vector is expressed can be changed.

    In addition to representing a Vector4DBasics, a ReferenceFrame is associated to a FrameVector4DBasics. This allows, for instance, to enforce, at runtime, that operations on vectors occur in the same coordinate system.

    Because a FrameVector4DBasics extends Vector4DBasics, it is compatible with methods only requiring Vector4DBasics. However, these methods do NOT assert that the operation occur in the proper coordinate system. Use this feature carefully and always prefer using methods requiring FrameVector4DBasics.
